id: pm-09rh
title: TypeScript-first extension & package scaffolding + SDK docs reframe
description: "Honor ADR pm-2c28 (extensions must be authored fully in TypeScript) by converting the pm extension/package init scaffolder to emit TypeScript source instead of plain .js, and reframing the SDK authoring docs/docstrings TypeScript-first. Today the scaffolder emits index.js with a single JSDoc @param annotation while every first-party package is TS (index.ts compiled to index.js). Scaffold index.ts + tsconfig.json + a build script + colocated index.test.ts, with the manifest entry pointing at the compiled ./index.js and the README documenting the install+build flow; update scaffold tests, smoke:external-packages, and dogfood:package-first to build the TS scaffold before loading. Reframe docs/SDK.md + docs/EXTENSIONS.md and the define*/compose* docstrings to justify the helpers by their TypeScript value (literal-type preservation + handler inference) rather than 'JS cannot annotate'."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 1
